-- Japanese Venture Starts Generating Power at Largest Solar Plant
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-11-05T05:05:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-05/japanese-venture-starts-generating-power-at-largest-solar-plant.html
Japan’s largest solar power station,
a 70 megawatt plant built by  Kyocera Corp. (6971)  and partners, began
generating power this month in the nation’s southwest, the
venture said.  The plant in Kagoshima prefecture is the biggest among the
country’s operating solar power stations, Kagoshima Mega Solar
Power Corp., the joint venture, said in a statement yesterday.  Other members of the venture are  KDDI Corp. (9433) ,  IHI Corp. (7013) ,
 Kyudenko Corp. (1959) , Bank of Kyoto Ltd., Kagoshima Bank Ltd., and
Takenaka Corp., according to the statement. The total investment
was 27 billion yen ($275 million).  Kyocera supplied panels for the plant, the venture said in
the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
